msgid "MLA page-size constraints:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:83
msgid "FlashInfer MLA: page_size = 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:84
msgid "FlashMLA: page_size = 64."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:85
msgid "Cutlass MLA: page_size = 128."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:86
msgid "TRTLLM MLA: page_size ∈ {32, 64}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:88
msgid "GDN Attention Backends"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:90
msgid ""
"GDN (Gated Delta Network) is a linear attention mechanism with O(n) "
"complexity, used in hybrid models that alternate GDN linear attention layers "
"with standard full attention layers. GDN is **not** selected via `--"
"attention-backend`; it is automatically activated when the model "
"architecture requires it (e.g., Qwen 3.5, Qwen 3 Next, Jet Nemotron, Jet "
"VLM)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/attention_backend.md:92
msgid ""
"The GDN linear attention layers have their own kernel backends, selected via "
"`--linear-attn-backend` (default: `triton`). You can override the kernel per "
"phase with `--linear-attn-decode-backend` and `--linear-attn-prefill-"
"backend`."
msgstr ""

